<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="O" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Offender" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Offender,</orth> 1) one that has wronged another: <cit><quote>the --'s sorrow lends but weak relief to him that bears the strong offence's cross,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 34.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 34, 11</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) one that has committed a sin or crime, a guilty person, a criminal: <bibl n="shak. luc 612" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 612</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 42.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 42, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.196" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 2, 196</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.2.116" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 2, 116</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 4.2.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 2, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.314" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 314</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.355" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. IV, 1, 355</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.1.204" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 1, 204</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 5.3.26" default="NO" valid="yes">All's V, 3, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 5.1.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 1, 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.2.8" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 2, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.5.15" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 5, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.1.216" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 1, 216</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.6.113" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 6, 113</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.1.130" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 1, 130</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.3.136" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 3, 136</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.1.203" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 203</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.122" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 122</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.122" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 122</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.122" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 122</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.4.67" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 4, 67</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.3.121" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 3, 121</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 2, 40</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.3.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 3, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 2.1.91" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 1, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.300" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 300</bibl>. With <emph>to</emph>: <cit><quote>as an o. to your father,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.2.81" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 2, 81</bibl></cit>.
